<exercise checkit-seed="0017" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>B= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 2 &amp; -4 &amp; 0 \\
-2 &amp; -3 &amp; 7 &amp; 0 \\
3 &amp; 1 &amp; -6 &amp; 2 \\
-1 &amp; -4 &amp; 7 &amp; 3
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>B^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
19 &amp; 20 &amp; 6 &amp; -4 \\
13 &amp; 12 &amp; 3 &amp; -2 \\
11 &amp; 11 &amp; 3 &amp; -2 \\
-2 &amp; -3 &amp; -1 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

